        "source": "slack",
        "channel": "proj-mobile-app-launch",
        "timestamp": "2025-11-05T17:10:00-05:00",
        "user": "alex.smith@company.com",
        "message": "@sam.williams quick one — I’m coordinating with Taylor to grab some time tomorrow morning with you and Jordan to align on the Mobile App Launch planning details (MOB-100/MOB-101 breakdown, scope, and dependencies). Thinking about a 45-min working session late morning.\n\nAre you generally okay with something in the 10:30–11:30 ET range, or do you have anything you absolutely can’t move there? I’ll wait for your thumbs-up before I send anything formal."
      },
      {
        "event_id": "planning_v4_slack_thread_1_reply_1",
        "source": "slack",
        "channel": "proj-mobile-app-launch",
        "timestamp": "2025-11-05T17:16:00-05:00",
        "user": "sam.williams@company.com",
        "message": "That window mostly works for me.\n\nI’ve got a 15-min 1:1 at 11:30 and would like a few minutes buffer beforehand, so if we could keep it bounded on the earlier side that’d be ideal.\n\nIf you aim for 10:30–11:15 ET for the Mobile App Launch sync with Jordan + me, I can make that work and come prepared with updated numbers and risk notes."
      },
      {
        "event_id": "planning_v4_slack_dm_1",
        "source": "slack",
        "channel": "DM_alex_jordan",
        "timestamp": "2025-11-05T17:28:00-05:00",
        "user": "alex.smith@company.com",
        "message": "Hey Jordan, looping you in async instead of spamming the channel.\n\nTaylor mentioned your afternoon is pretty packed tomorrow, so I’m trying to grab a short morning working session focused just on the Mobile App Launch planning bits.\n\nWould you be able to join a ~45-min sync with Sam and me tomorrow starting at 10:30 ET? The idea is to:\n- walk through the open planning items on MOB-100 and MOB-101\n- confirm what’s realistic to commit for the first development milestone\n- surface any backend dependencies we might be underestimating\n\nIf 10:30–11:15 ET is a no-go for you, is there any other morning slot (between 10:00–12:00) that you could do with Sam? I’m trying hard to keep this in the morning before all the deployment work kicks off."
      },
