        "project_key": "MOB",
        "issue_key": "MOB-101",
        "author": "alex.smith@company.com",
        "comment": "Weekly update (week of Nov 3):\n\n- Performance: After the last round of optimizations that Jordan landed, cold start on the Android beta build is down by ~14–15% compared to last week’s baseline. iOS is seeing a similar ~15% improvement in median app launch time on our test devices.\n- User metrics: Early beta cohort is growing steadily; active testers are up by roughly 9–10% week-over-week as we expanded the invite list.\n\nThese are encouraging signals ahead of the upcoming Mobile App Launch milestones. We’ll include more detail in the PM weekly summary email."
      },
      {
        "event_id": "weekly_report_doc_1",
        "source": "doc",
        "timestamp": "2025-11-07T14:20:00-05:00",
        "author": "alex.smith@company.com",
        "title": "Mobile App – Weekly Wins (Week of Nov 3)",
        "doc_id": "doc_mob_weekly_wins_2025_11_07",
        "content": "Mobile App – Weekly Wins (Week of Nov 3)\nOwner: Alex Smith (PM)\nProject: MOB – Mobile App Launch\nWeek ending: 2025-11-07\n\nSummary\nThis week we saw solid improvements on both performance and early user metrics as we get closer to the Mobile App Launch.\n\nKey Wins\n1) Performance improvements\n- The latest round of optimizations to startup paths and network calls reduced end-to-end app launch time by approximately 15% versus last week’s build.\n- This improvement is consistent across the majority of our test devices (Android and iOS), with a noticeable reduction in time-to-first-interaction.\n\n2) Early user growth\n- Our beta tester base grew by about 10% week-over-week after we opened up additional invite codes.\n- Engagement from the expanded cohort has remained healthy; no drop-off in daily active testers so far.\n\n3) Readiness for upcoming launch milestones\n- The performance gains and steady beta growth put us in a better position going into the Planning and Development milestones for the Mobile App Launch.\n\nNext Steps\n- Continue to monitor performance as new features are integrated.\n- Prepare a more detailed breakdown of performance and user metrics for the broader stakeholder review next week."
      },
      {
        "event_id": "weekly_report_email_1",
        "source": "email",
        "timestamp": "2025-11-07T16:45:00-05:00",
        "from": "alex.smith@company.com",
        "to": [
          "rnd-team@company.com",
          "eng-mobile@company.com"
        ],
        "cc": [
          "taylor.brown@company.com",
          "sam.williams@company.com"
        ],
        "subject": "[MOB] Weekly Wins – Performance & Beta User Growth (week of Nov 3)",
        "body": "Hi all,\n\nSharing a quick summary of this week’s wins for the Mobile App Launch (MOB):\n\n1) Performance improvements\n- Thanks to the latest optimizations from the engineering team, app startup times improved by roughly 15% compared to last week’s baseline across our primary test devices.\n- This should give us more breathing room as we layer in additional launch-critical features.\n\n2) Early user growth\n- Our beta user base grew by about 10% week-over-week after we expanded invite distribution.\n- Engagement from the new cohort looks strong so far, with no notable drop-off in daily active testers.\n\nThese gains are encouraging as we head into the next Planning and Development milestones for MOB. More detailed breakdowns are captured in the “Mobile App – Weekly Wins (Week of Nov 3)” doc if you’d like to dig deeper.\n\nHave a good weekend,\nAlex"
      }
    ]
  }
